{
  "text": "Value added and capital have a positive and significant effect, indicating a direct relationship between these variables and CO 2 emissions. Therefore, higher economic activity generates a higher level of CO 2 emissions. This finding is consistent with the results of Tsai (2010, 2011) in the context of the BRIC countries, with the results of [CITATION_1] in the Asia-Pacific region and with the results of Wang (2011) in developed and developing countries.",
